				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: NEW!!!! i want a bard. <a name="31881"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 31 04 8:12 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Funny but I find stamina quite easy to max and struggle more with charisma (though LDoN augs help, nobody else wants cha augs!). Charisma has been proven to reduce missed notes, and will also lead to less critical lull failures (with better charisma, if a mob resists lull it is less likely to aggro, giving you a second chance)
<br />

<br />
Stamina will give more hp, but at lower levels the effect is small and outweighed by buying some hp gear, and at higher levels with buffs you'll be maxing it out anyway.
<br />

<br />
As for race it really doesn't matter much. Kitties are at a disadvantage with cultural armour but its not the be all and end all. Humans can't see anything in the dark. Half-Elf bards are everywhere. At the end of the day there are two or three easily obtained illusion items so you can change what race you are anyway<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Me, I'm a kitty and purrfectly happy with my choice <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Whatever you do I suggest staying Agnostic. An agnostic bard with faction song and a few illusions can enter a lot more player cities than one who worships a deity. Ok, so not a massive issue really but I like being able to roam around <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
