				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: NEW!!!! i want a bard. <a name="31906"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 31 04 9:25 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Spec? I smell a former DAoC player!
<br />

<br />
Anyway, it's all pretty simple:
<br />

<br />
Kitty Bard - Have to find litter boxes all the time and get blood stuck in their fur.
<br />
Wood Elf Bard - More into how they look than actually doing their job.
<br />
Human Bard - Always stumbled around blindly in the dark whining abotu finding a Wisp to kill.
<br />
Half Elf Bard - Strong, charismatic, natural leaders, best looking.. you get the idea!
<br />

<br />
As for starting stats.. two schools of thought on that and pretty much depends on your future plans:
<br />
- The Stamina thought: All points into Stamina, leftovers probably Charisma. Get as many HPs as you can get, probably best if you do not plan on seeing the end game.
<br />
- The Charisma/Dex thought: This is better if you plan on getting end-game equipment, as Stamina can easily be maxed. Dex and Charisma are both handy for Bards.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I used to be Stamina all the way.. but if I created a Bard now I would go for Charisma/Dex.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
