Superb generalisation /golfclap
<br />

<br />
You realise how stupid we used to look wearing a helm in the old days? And how it looked like we literally had no butt? I sank down on my knees and wept with joy the day Luclin models were introduced.
<br />

<br />
Stamina is what most pump their starting points into. When I started, I didn't intend to get hit much, and I still don't. Having a heap of HPs doesn't exactly encourage sharp thinking and reflexes in every person that chooses a bard when they're levelling up. There's time and drops later on to stack the HPs for the big encounters.
<br />

<br />
I spread points through dex, cha and agi and I'm still happy with that.</span></td>
