			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: NEW!!!! i want a bard. <a name="31940"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 31 04 10:54 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">- The Charisma/Dex thought: This is better if you plan on getting end-game equipment, as Stamina can easily be maxed. Dex and Charisma are both handy for Bards.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This is the school of thought I follow.  The people advocating stamina have been hanging around the monastery too long.  I think avoiding a missed note (dexterity), charm break or critical lull failure (charisma) is more important for a bard than the hitpoints gained from putting points into stamina.
<br />

<br />
Regarding the Casters Realm guide, basically it advocates splitting points between charisma and dexterity, with a slight preference for dex.  For the weakling elves it advises putting a few points into strength.  I see nothing wrong with this.  Besides, I have yet to find another guide anywhere on the internet that gives <i>specific</i> advice on where to place starting points for each race.  If there is one, someone please post it.
<br />

<br />
Finally, with the gear available in the game now and alternate advancement, I don't think where you put your starting points is critical in the long term scheme of things.  An argument can be made to support anything, but before your head explodes, Seryu, and you go running, screaming back to Dark Age of Camelot or whatever, try to just keep it simple: pick a race and a deity, then use the Casters Realm guide.  You'll be fine.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
