				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: NEW!!!! i want a bard. <a name="31960"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 31 04 12:04 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Dex was the first stat that I maxed followed by strength.  These two stats are on most gear to some degree and I wouldn't put points into them.  Buffs can easily make up for any lack of stats.  
<br />

<br />
As a bard, you could make a point for any stat being important except wisdom.  I've found stamina to be the hardest to raise myself, although, with LDoN and the later expansions, it has been much easier.  
<br />

<br />
I went with a human bard for two reasons.  First, they have balanced starting stats.  Secondly, there weren't/aren't alot of human bards.  The blindness of being a human blows, but there are items, augs, and illusions that can fix that easily.  Once you learn your way around, being blind isn't even an issue really.
<br />

<br />
For religion, I didn't know any better and choose Errollis Marr.  If there was one thing I could change, it would be my religion to Agnostic.  While it hasn't hindered me really, with illusions, agnostic would be a convenience .
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
